Author: Crypto Mission
Content:
? Bitget Wallet Launches Ecosystem Fund Along with Onchain Layer

? Bitget plans to develop its own blockchain ecosystem, similar to those of Binance, OKX, and KuCoin.

? Bitget will launch an Onchain layer in collaboration with DApp developers and has established a $10 million BWB ecosystem fund to accelerate this project.

? BWB is the native token of the Bitget wallet, similar to the $TWT token, and can be used to cover transaction fees.

? The Bitget OnChain Layer Ecosystem Fund will initially focus on investing in and incubating Web3 trading services, including price aggregators, on-chain derivatives markets, and trading bots.

? Bitget Wallet is one of the more popular self-custodial wallets in the Asia-Pacific region, with over 20 million users. The BWB token, set to be introduced this quarter, will play a key role in the Bitget ecosystem.

Author: Jeremiah LivingSpring
Content:
An Open Letter to @ton_blockchain:

Hi, I'm Jeremiah LivingSpring, and I write on behalf of the entire TON community in Nigeria, and Africa at large.

Damx (@damxton) is a fully fledged TON Professional.

He is the most passionate member of the TON community in Nigeria and in all of Africa.

As the Founder of @TonNomads, he has garnered over 100 thousand people on Telegram, actively participating in his channel; this alone has created massive visibility and adoption for the TON ecosystem in Africa.

Damx, is completely immersed in everything TON! His profile on X and Telegram defines The Open Network, through and through; he never deviates. 

Amidst being the biggest TON Promoter in all of Africa, he's also the most learned in all things TON, in the continent, yes. 

Nigeria especially, and Africa at large, needs a representative from home soil in the Ton Foundation.

So, we have selected a candidate:

On behalf of the TON community in Nigeria, the nation with the most active and populous TON community in the African continent, and on behalf of the same community in Africa at large, I petition to you, @ton_blockchain, to induct Damx into the Ton Foundation, to be our representative and to be an active contributor to the The Open Network.

This is a unified petition; the entire TON community in Nigeria, and Africa at large, is behind it. 

To conclude this petition, I remark:

The contributions of Damx to the The Open Network will be important & actionable; he is smart, knowledgeable, creative, influential, and committed to the TON ecosystem. He will be an excellent addition to the Ton Foundation, most certainly.

We're looking forward to hearing from you, and most importantly, seeing Damx inducted into the Ton Foundation. 

Thank you. 

Jeremiah LivingSpring, on behalf of TON Nigeria, and Africa.

Our scalable Bitcoin L2 infrastructure supports complex AI tasks and seamless AI integration, powered by high-performance GPUs for training advanced AI agents.

Author: Yvonne Kagondu
Content:
I'm getting a lot of questions on opportunities in the digital space. I haven't responded to them because it's such a long topic.

I don't know if we can have an X space to discuss this more. For me, I specialised in Blockchain opportunities. 

In Blockchain alone I can say:
- trading: P2P trading (popular in Kenya), spot trading, derivatives trading, arbitrage trading etc
- software smart contract development 
- community management and building 
- becoming a founder
- becoming a KOL
- Airdrop hunting
- design
- auditing
- becoming a writer (blog or technical writer)
- memecoins 
- HODLing
Just to mention a few.

When I look at other industries, I see more opportunities there. I have seen people becoming influencers on various social media platforms, vloggers, I have seen people build their skills online and monetize them, like baking or makeup. I know too many online writers, transcribers and people working on Upwork, Fiverr and the likes. I know people who operate their business fully online.

I am also sure that there are new online jobs being created that we don't know yet.

I am almost sure there are many forums online that discuss these. Many are on YouTube. As said earlier, we need to open our eyes, open our minds, open our laptops.

Author: Layer 2 BNB
Content: The BNB Layer 2 project is an extension platform of the Binance Smart Chain (BSC), designed to enhance the scalability and performance of the blockchain. Layer 2 helps reduce network congestion and increase transaction speed by moving some activities to a beneficial secondary layer. This helps minimize costs and waiting times for transactions, as well as enhance the scalability of the system. BNB Layer 2 promises to deliver faster transaction experiences, lower costs, and stronger scalability for BSC users.

Author: Robert Sasu
Content:
Building on #blockchain has never been easier and is getting even more streamlined for app builders.

#Swift is super easy. It can do everything for Apple devices and for more. Swift can be compiled to WASM which is needed for the smart contract execution on MultiversX.

WASM is the way to go for general purpose blockchains which want to be the general open computer for the world. Build everything with any language and deploy it on WASM.

Congrats @gfusee33 for making the framework happen!

This SDK will work so well with the new account abstraction model designed for passkeys, thus for mobile apps without seedphrases. The perfect match to build #web3 apps which feel and look like the best apps from the web2 world.

New collection “Mass”

Content:
Chaos Unleashed: OverTrip's Next Chapter Revealed ?

OverTrip is not your ordinary web3 game. It’s a blend of high-octane battle royale action, immersive gameplay, and blockchain technology, set against the backdrop of a trippy, neon-infused universe.

The Founders' Pass: Your Ticket to the Adventure

Exclusive In-Game Benefits: Holders enjoy early access to game features, special in-game assets, and enhanced staking/wagering experiences.

$TRIP Airdrops: Airdrops of $TRIP tokens, enriching your gaming journey and offering additional ways to earn within the ecosystem. More information on this later revealing tokenomics and more!

Community and Governance: Be part of an exclusive community with a say in the game's development, access to special events, and the opportunity to shape the future of OverTrip.

The Game and Its Ecosystem

OverTrip's gameplay is designed to be as exhilarating as its visual appeal. Players engage in a skill-based battle royale, staking $TRIP tokens, and competing for glory in a variety of game modes. The game features:

Instant Play System: Jump straight into action with an instant play system that matches you in battles without delay.

Diverse Game Modes: From solo to squad modes, each offering a different taste of chaos and strategy.

Dynamic Maps: Battle across terrains designed for cunning, allowing sneaky tactics and bold confrontations.

$TRIP Token: The Currency of Chaos

$TRIP tokens are at the heart of OverTrip's play-to-earn model, serving multiple functions within the ecosystem:

Staking in Battles: Stake your $TRIP in matches, with victors taking the pot.

In-Game Purchases: Use $TRIP to buy in-game items, assets, and unlock special features.

Community Rewards: Participate in airdrop farming campaigns and community challenges to earn more $TRIP.

What Comes Next

The sell-out of the Founders' Pass is just the beginning. Here's what holders and the broader community can look forward to:

Detailed Gameplay Reveal Trailer: Get a closer look at the action-packed gameplay and immersive world of OverTrip.

Trippy Terminal Launch: The central hub for all things OverTrip, including missions for points, $TRIP farming, and exclusive content.

$TRIP Airdrop Campaigns: Stay tuned for the launch of airdrop farming campaigns, offering everyone a chance to earn $TRIP and engage with the game before its official release.

? Blockchain Data Revolution: 
Our unique approach includes an Online Data Studio for managed crypto data and an Offline Data Sync integration for privacy-focused self-hosted infrastructure, ensuring versatility and security.

???Technological Innovations:
1. Our Streaming Data Warehouse Architecture redefines data freshness and depth.

? Impressive Growth:
1. Achieved a 10X increase in developer engagement.
2. Facilitated the creation of over 10,000 projects within our ecosystem.
3. Efficiently managed over 200 million daily backend data requests.

Author: DogePunks
Content:
Informative and educational post regarding the Ordinals:

Technically, a collector of Ordinals NFTs possesses the exclusive control of a specific satoshi on the Bitcoin blockchain to which unique data has been attached using the "inscription" technique. 

Here is a detailed explanation:

1. Possession of Satoshi: The collector holds a Bitcoin address containing the uniquely numbered satoshi. This satoshi is identified through Ordinal Theory, which assigns a sequential number to every existing satoshi.

2. Associated Data (Inscription): This satoshi has additional data, such as images, texts, videos, or any other type of digital content, inscribed on it. These data are written directly onto the Bitcoin blockchain, making them permanent and immutable.

3. Control of the Satoshi: The collector has the private key to the Bitcoin address holding the satoshi with the inscription. This allows them to transfer the satoshi (and thus the NFT) to another Bitcoin address, selling or trading it just like any other Bitcoin transaction.

4. Uniqueness and Immutability: Since each satoshi with an inscription is unique and immutable, the collector owns a unique piece of digital content guaranteed by the security and decentralization of the Bitcoin network.

5. Visualization and Interaction: The collector can view the data associated with their Ordinal NFT through tools and platforms that support this type of NFT on Bitcoin. These tools can read the Bitcoin blockchain and present the data in a comprehensible and visible format .

In summary, the collector possesses a unique digital asset represented by a specific satoshi on the Bitcoin blockchain, with unique data inscribed on it, ensuring ownership and authenticity through the security of the Bitcoin network.

This post was structured to help those entering this world, was it helpful?

WOOF!
